From a cursory glance, this seems like mostly useless syntactic sugar. I don't exactly see what is the functional different between<p><pre><code>  module A {
    export var myPublic = 1
    var myPrivate = 2
  }
</code></pre>
and<p><pre><code>  var A = new function() {
    this.myPublic = 1
    var myPrivate = 2
  }
</code></pre>
except that the first will clash with a bunch of existing script that use "module" and "export" as variable names. And the idea of making "load" a keyword in page 26 is just plain silly.
